{
  "id": "019cf122-3f35-75a2-a3b1-2b53a77233aa",
  "content": "## embedding_backend config field — design decision\n\n### Decision\nAdded `embedding_backend: String` to InferenceConfig alongside the existing `backend: String`. This allows specifying different GPU backends for embedding (ONNX/fastembed) vs chat (llama.cpp) models — needed because OpenVINO supports ONNX but NOT llama.cpp.\n\n### Rationale\nWith both NVIDIA GPU (CUDA for chat) and Intel iGPU (OpenVINO for ONNX embedding) available, we want to use both simultaneously. The existing single `backend` field couldn't express this split. A dedicated `embedding_backend` field (falling back to `backend` when empty) is the minimal change.\n\n### Implementation\n- InferenceConfig.embedding_backend: String (serde default = \"\")\n- inference_provisioner::load_models: uses `effective_embed_backend = if embedding_backend.is_empty() { backend } else { embedding_backend }`\n- ensure_ready: threads embedding_backend through to load_models\n- Both ensure_ready call sites in corvia-cli/src/main.rs updated\n- corvia.toml: `embedding_backend = \"openvino\"` with `backend = \"cuda\"` → Intel iGPU for nomic-embed-text, NVIDIA for qwen3\n\n### Not changed\n- reload_models still uses single backend (acceptable for CLI reload command)\n- No proto changes needed — LoadModelRequest.backend field reused with per-model value\n- backend.rs resolve_explicit_backend already rejects openvino for chat model_type\n\n### Status\nCommitted to repos/corvia master (2026-03-15). Awaiting GitHub release + install_binaries to activate in devcontainer.\n",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
  "workstream": "main",
